								Welcome To ForkRF :

"  ForkRF aims to parrellize the Random Forest code inorder to get higher performance "
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~


i) Here large data sets say KDDCUP99.CORRECTED.data of 718 MB is splitted in 2.5 MB 
ii) This is done by SplitString.java
iii) Split.java is character spliiter (Very slower )
iv) SplitRF.java uses WEKA random forest library 
v) Logs the output of each spliited datasets
vi) Then Transmitter transmits the splitted files to various distributed systems
vii) Recever receive sthe file computes the RF and returns back the result 

Proposed works : Extending the Random Forest and splitting with JCUDA programming ( 40 times faster than existing code ;-) )

Thanks for your Interest !